						               													<description>Springsign is a town-building resource-management game for 1-6 players, ages 14 and up.  The game retails for $40, but we want to offer it to our Kickstarter backers for $35. Over the course of a ~1-2 hour game, the players will act as councilors, local leaders, and generally important personages in a growing frontier settlement. Right now, Springsign is a &amp;quot;quaint&amp;quot; little town (some might even say &amp;quot;dead-end&amp;quot; or &amp;quot;completely-untamable&amp;quot;), but under the right leadership its potential is limitless. Together, the players will need to grow the town by constructing new buildings, keeping settlers fed, and fending off the many bandits that skulk around town. There's only one catch:&amp;#10;This is not a cooperative game!&amp;#10;Sure it's all hands on deck now, but when the townsfolk start to look for a mayor, who will they choose? As the players develop town, they'll also have to outmaneuver and outwit one another to garner more support. Votes can be bought with good deeds and hard work... or through &amp;quot;less honest&amp;quot; means. Perhaps you'll use your lumber to construct new and better buildings for the townsfolk, earning yourself their favor. Alternatively, perhaps you'll use the building one of your opponents built to ship contraband out of town, earning you a different kind of power.&amp;#10;When the chips are down, will you do what's right for Springsign, or will you push your opponents out of power? Those greedy enough to steal victory from their opponents will be able to win, and some players may be willing to risk the town itself in their race to the top!&amp;#10;Springsign is made for families and hard-core gamers alike - all kinds of players will find something to enjoy. Springsign is highly replayable thanks to its modular nature. Every game will see a different combination of settlers, buildings, and available food that steers the game in unexpected directions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
